### P4: Service-boundary decision (agent-coordinator) ‚Äî ‚úÖ DONE

**Question**: Should `agent-coordinator` (61 .py files, port 9001, Core Service: No) remain a separate microservice, or fold into `coordinator-api` (485 .py files, port 8203, Core Service: Yes)?

**Decision**: **Keep agent-coordinator as a separate microservice.**

**Rationale** (documented in <ref_file file="/opt/aitbc/docs/releases/v0.5.13/agent_coordinator_boundary.md" />):

| Coupling dimension | Finding |
|--------------------|---------|
| coordinator-api ‚Üí agent-coordinator API calls | **Zero** ‚Äî all 7 files referencing port 9001 use it only in CORS `allow_origins`, not as HTTP client targets |
| agent-coordinator ‚Üí coordinator-api API calls | **Zero** ‚Äî only reference is `COORDINATOR_API_KEY` env var name, not a URL |
| Shared database | **No** ‚Äî agent-coord uses own SQLite (`agent_coin_requests.db`, stdlib sqlite3), coordinator-api uses SQLAlchemy (`coordinator.db`) |
| Shared Redis | Same instance, **different logical DBs** (db 1 vs db 0) |
| systemd dependency | Independent units, different dependency chains (agent-coord depends on Redis, coordinator-api does not) |
| External clients | CLI calls agent-coordinator directly at `localhost:9001` for agent discovery/registration |

Folding in would require migrating 61 files + 103 endpoints, merging two DBs, repointing CLI, merging two auth systems ‚Äî high blast radius for zero coupling reduction.

**Additional findings**:
- `apps/agent-coordinator/README.md` already existed ‚Äî file count corrected (48‚Üí61)
- Deployment gap: `aitbc-agent-coordinator.service` file exists but is NOT symlinked into `/etc/systemd/system/` (unlike the 12 other aitbc services verified in B7)

**Files**: `docs/releases/v0.5.13/agent_coordinator_boundary.md`, `apps/agent-coordinator/README.md`

